<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<section xml:id="inv-5-10">
  <title>Investigation 5.10: Running Out of Time</title>

  <exercises xml:id="exercises5-10" hidden-label="yes">
    <title>The Study</title>

    <p>Data from a local 5K race include age and finish time for 248 runners. The goal is to assess whether finish time changes with age.</p>

    <exercise xml:id="inv5-10-a" label="I5.10.a"><title>Identify Variables</title><statement><p>(a) Identify explanatory and response variables.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="inv5-10-b" label="I5.10.b"><title>Conjecture Direction and Form</title><statement><p>(b) Predict direction, linearity, and likely significance of association.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="inv5-10-c" label="I5.10.c"><title>Scatterplot and Data Features</title><statement><p>(c) Plot finish time vs age and discuss unusual features/outliers.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="inv5-10-d" label="I5.10.d"><title>Refit Without Outlier</title><statement><p>(d) Remove outlier and report regression equation and slope interpretation.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="inv5-10-e" label="I5.10.e"><title>Sampling-Variability Question</title><statement><p>(e) Could observed slope arise by chance if no population association exists? Outline investigation approach.</p></statement><response/></exercise>

    <assemblage>
      <title>Terminology Detour</title>
      <p>Use <m>b_0, b_1</m> for sample intercept/slope and <m>\beta_0, \beta_1</m> for population parameters.</p>
    </assemblage>

    <exercise xml:id="inv5-10-f" label="I5.10.f"><title>Hypotheses for Slope</title><statement><p>(f) State null and alternative hypotheses for testing whether finish time changes with age.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="inv5-10-g" label="I5.10.g"><title>Compute Sample Summaries</title><statement><p>(g) Obtain means, SDs, and regression residual SD from data.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="inv5-10-h" label="I5.10.h"><title>Design Null Population</title><statement><p>(h) Build a null population with <m>\beta_1=0</m> and matching sample characteristics; draw one sample and compare slopes.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="inv5-10-i" label="I5.10.i"><title>Second Sample and Variability</title><statement><p>(i) Draw another sample; compare regression line and discuss sampling variability.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="inv5-10-j" label="I5.10.j"><title>Many Sample Lines</title><statement><p>(j) Draw many sample lines and describe variation pattern.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="inv5-10-k" label="I5.10.k"><title>Null Distribution of Slopes</title><statement><p>(k) Describe shape, center, and SD of null slope distribution.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="inv5-10-l" label="I5.10.l"><title>Expected Center</title><statement><p>(l) Is center as expected under null? Explain.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="inv5-10-m" label="I5.10.m"><title>Change Sigma</title><statement><p>(m) Reduce sigma and describe population scatterplot change.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="inv5-10-n" label="I5.10.n"><title>Predict Effect of Sigma Change</title><statement><p>(n) Predict effect on slope distribution.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="inv5-10-o" label="I5.10.o"><title>Check Sigma Prediction</title><statement><p>(o) Simulate and evaluate prediction from part (n).</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="inv5-10-p" label="I5.10.p"><title>Change SD(X)</title><statement><p>(p) Modify SD(X); predict effect on slope and intercept sampling distributions.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="inv5-10-q" label="I5.10.q"><title>Check SD(X) Prediction</title><statement><p>(q) Simulate and evaluate predictions from part (p).</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="inv5-10-r" label="I5.10.r"><title>Change Sample Size</title><statement><p>(r) Reduce sample size and predict effect on slope distribution.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="inv5-10-s" label="I5.10.s"><title>Check Sample Size Prediction</title><statement><p>(s) Simulate and evaluate prediction from part (r).</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="inv5-10-t" label="I5.10.t"><title>Summarize Effects</title><statement><p>(t) Summarize effects of sigma, SD(X), and n on slope sampling distribution.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="inv5-10-u" label="I5.10.u"><title>Intuition</title><statement><p>(u) Explain intuitively why these effects occur.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="inv5-10-v" label="I5.10.v"><title>Formula Consistency</title><statement><p>(v) Compare simulation behavior to formula for SD of slope estimator.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="inv5-10-w" label="I5.10.w"><title>Observed Slope Under Null</title><statement><p>(w) Locate observed slope in null distribution and estimate p-value.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="inv5-10-x" label="I5.10.x"><title>Alternative Null Slope</title><statement><p>(x) Repeat simulation for a nonzero null slope and assess plausibility.</p></statement><response/></exercise>

    <assemblage>
      <title>Study Conclusions</title>
      <p>These data typically provide strong evidence that finish time and age are associated in this runner population context; large observed slope values are highly unlikely under a no-association model.</p>
    </assemblage>

    <exercise xml:id="inv5-10-y" label="I5.10.y"><title>Estimate Sigma</title><statement><p>(y) Suggest how to estimate population residual SD from sample data.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="inv5-10-z" label="I5.10.z"><title>Standardize Slope</title><statement><p>(z) Compute standardized slope statistic.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="inv5-10-aa" label="I5.10.aa"><title>Technology Confirmation</title><statement><p>(aa) Confirm t-statistic and p-value with technology output.</p></statement><response/></exercise>

    <exercise xml:id="inv5-10-practice-a" label="I5.10A"><title>Practice Problem 5.10A</title><statement><p>Repeat analysis without removing outlier and compare results.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="inv5-10-practice-b" label="I5.10B"><title>Practice Problem 5.10B</title><statement><p>Compare unofficial and official race files and reassess evidence strength.</p></statement><response/></exercise>
  </exercises>
</section>
